    "body": "Deja vu :) https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/13157#discussion_r821509725\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/3e8647d626004852428a856fdd78369975ae13f9/src/status_im2/common/theme/core.cljs#L8-L9\r\n\r\n> One solution can be to check if theme applied by event is same as app, just ignore it and don't reload UI\r\n\r\nWe already have [check](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/3e8647d626004852428a856fdd78369975ae13f9/src/status_im2/common/theme/core.cljs#L13) for this, but in [old bug](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/13157) problem was that event fired twice when app returned from background, once with wrong value and once with correct value. So we used [solution](https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/28525#issuecomment-841812810) where we ignored value provided by event itself and manually requested value. But its not working anymore for some reason.\r\n\r\n",
